Koi herpesvirus disease, Italy
------------------------------
Information received on [and dated] 3 Dec 2018 from Dr Silvio Borrello, Chief Veterinary Officer, Food Safety and Collegial Bodies for Health Protection, Ministry of Health, Department for Veterinary Public Health, Rome, Italy

Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 30 Ag 2018
Date of confirmation of the event: 24 Oct 2018
Reason for notification: Recurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: 22 Dec 2017
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: Koi herpesvirus
Nature of diagnosis: clinical, laboratory (advanced)
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country.

New outbreaks (1)
Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak 1 (KOI_TO_2018_1): Cumiana, Torino, Piemonte
Date of start of the outbreak: 30 Aug 2018
Outbreak status: continuing or date resolved not provided
Epidemiological unit: farm
Water type: fresh water
Population type: wild
Production system: semi-closed
Total animals affected:
Species / Morbidity / Mortality / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered
Carp (_Cyprinus carpio_) / 3.2%/ 3.2%) / 320 / 10 / 10 / - / -
Affected population: clinical symptoms appeared on [30 Aug 2018] in a pond which is not connected with any stream and is used only for recreational purposes.
Outbreak statistics [rates apparent, expressed as percentages]
Species / Morbidity rate / Mortality rate / Case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Carp (_Cyprinus carpio_) / 3.13% / 3.13% / 100% / **
*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction, and/or slaughter
** Not calculated because of missing information

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive

Control measures
Measures applied: movement control inside the country, vaccination permitted (if a vaccine exists), no treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied: no other measures

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type / Species / Test / Test date / Result
Experimental Zooprophylactic Institute (IZS), Padova (National laboratory) / Carp (_Cyprinus carpio_) / nested RT- PCR / 24 Oct 2018 / Positive
Experimental Zooprophylactic Institute (IZS), Padova (National laboratory) / Carp (_Cyprinus carpio_) / real-time PCR / 24 Oct 2018 / Positive

Future reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

[The location of the outbreak can be seen on the interactive map included in the OIE report at the source URL above.]

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[Koi herpesvirus disease (KHVD) is a herpesvirus infection capable of inducing a contagious and acute viraemia in common carp (_Cyprinus carpio_) and varieties such as koi carp and ghost carp (http://www.oie.int/index.php?id=2439&L=0&htmfile=chapitre_koi_herpesvirus.htm).

In September 2017, Italy reported an event of Koi herpesvirus disease; 3 outbreaks were reported. The event was resolved on 22 Dec 2017, see event summary and updated map at http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review/viewsummary?fupser=&dothis=&reportid=24860. - Mod.CRD

HealthMap/ProMED-mail map of Italy: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=6178641,64719]
